title.narrative: Helping Address Rural Vulnerabilities and Ecosystem STability (HARVEST)

description.narrative: (Cambodia): -The project seeks to reduce poverty and malnutrition rates in four provinces by diversifying food production and increasing incomes for up to 70,000 rural households. By training farmers and community forest members while advancing policy reforms, USAID aims to improve rice production, aquaculture and horticulture value-chains, protect biodiversity, and support Cambodia's Enhancing Capacity for Low Emissions Development Strategy. With FY 2014 funds, the program will continue to introduce farming techniques to diversify crops and reduce emissions from rice production; help households adapt to climate change and build resiliency; improve food availability by strengthening key value-chains; and train local agriculture technicians to help farmers adopt good agricultural practices. Starting in FY 2014, the project will scale-up commercial horticulture to an additional 10,000 farmers and increase the resiliency and incomes of a greater number of poor and vulnerable populations.
